reviews.title: Poor costly experience
reviews.text:
First I did some glow golf.
Then got 5 chips for free drinks.
At home comes the receipt checked but got 2 free drinks, strange.
American and Italian burgers ordered.
Meat was cold and dry.
Salad was sour.
The fries tasted like it was baked twice so chewy.
The milkshake tasted like syrup and way too sweet.
In short, once but never again!

reviews.title: Fantastic afternoon!
reviews.text:
Delicious lunch with two families (9 in total).
Can't say otherwise as a top experience!
Friendly staff, excellent food, spacious layout, clean toilets.
(oh yes the flushing buttons of the urinals were gone, but nevertheless fine).
Price/quality really fine, good portions
Followed by a round of glow golf, great fun!
All in all a Sunday afternoon well spent.
Parking in the area incidentally free on Sundays, very busy but can score a spot.

reviews.title: Sergio golfs through hell
reviews.text:
I harbour mixed emotions for this establishment. 

We walked in for some refreshment, upon paying I realised we had been slapped with a hefty tariff of €31 for three measly pints. That’s not even London prices. This was a financial burden almost too much to bear (sorry Gran no heating for this month). 

After I’d grounded myself with Native American breathing techniques (self taught, obviously, after being attacked by what can only be described as a rather large bee) I went to pay for the golf. 

I asked how much it cost, ‘€13 for the golf and a drink’, excellent I thought. The gentlemen then gestured to a cooler filled with zesty beverages, and I smelt something foul in the air, a lie so cruel. 

In my naivety I assumed my nose would be playing tricks on me, alas, this was not the case. I was informed that each drink had an individual price on top of the 13.50 for glow golf. Being a newly divorced man I opted for the Duvel 6.66 as it was by far the strongest available. Upon bringing this to the till I was informed this would be an additional €7, to say I was outraged was an understatement.

This establishment is so foul that it smells like a dead badger rotting on the M5. Corruption here is rife, much like dry rot in a Victorian house, it can only be removed by demolishing completely and starting from scratch - killing the weed at the root, genesis. 

That being said, the building itself is beautifully furnished while the glowgolf as an activity is an entertaining way to lose some brain cells and kill an hour. The addition of the 3D glasses added a layer of excitement that I haven’t felt since ‘that’ night in Istanbul.

reviews.title: Don’t Go Here
reviews.text:
Very Disappointed.

Mini Golf was not as expected, needs to be refurbished.

Our table was dirty and we had to ask twice for it to be cleaned. We waited around 10 minutes for the table to be cleaned. The girl who served us our drinks seen the dirty table and didn’t do anything about it.

When our table was eventually cleaned we had to move as the smell of the rag the boy used to clean our table smelled horrible and left a nasty wet smell on the table.

The games are falling apart, missing pieces and not enjoyable to play at all.

reviews.title: Top experience
reviews.text: We had dinner here tonight. It was top the staff was incredibly friendly and very fast. After dinner we went miniature golf very nice very varying courses so it does not get bored. Definitely recommended!

reviews.title: Tasty!
reviews.text: Super tasty food and a nice American looking restaurant. We then also went to the adjacent glow wave, highly recommended!

reviews.title: Like being in Hollywood
reviews.text: Service, atmosphere, food and drinks superb. Nice atmosphere with all those Disney and Hollywood characters around you. Management looks after you carefully. Music is pleasant. And the food is very tasty

reviews.title: Excellent Restaurant
reviews.text: Dinner at the cafe was wonderful. We were at least 30 years older than the other guests but that didn't matter. Spacious, clean and modern restaurant. Menu has lots of choices of food and beverages at really good prices. Games available whilst seated. Meals were delicious and service was friendly and professional. Will return. Presentation excellent.

reviews.title: Shane about the customer service!
reviews.text: Golf was good. Adults and kids enjoyed. It’s a bit different. 18 holes although one closed. Could do with a bit of an upgrade and some neon paint so that the holes stand out. On the other hand the service is awful. The drinks are either ridiculously priced or we were ripped off. For the golf they asked for ID for our kids that were all 11/12. Because we didn’t have it they were all charged full. They just want to make maximum money. No smiles or customer skills whatsoever. It’s a shame as with a bit of investment and new staff it could be a gold mine!

reviews.title: Competitive fun
reviews.text: Great to visit for some competitive fun! Bar upstairs as well which means you can have a drink before, after or whilst playing! Course can take anywhere from 45 minutes onwards which a few challenging holes!

reviews.title: Superb Experience!
reviews.text: The service was great, the staff were extremely polite, and it was overall a fun experience. There’s also an arcade right next to it which you can go to after.

reviews.title: A lot of fun!
reviews.text:
Everyone loves crazy/mini golf but they can be a bit mixed in quality this 15 hole indoor one is good fun.

We had a bite to eat first then played a round, some tricky holes and some easier. Worth a visit.

reviews.title: Terrible family experience with this unhygienic  and unfriendly place!
reviews.text: Terrible service, filthy table and very unfriendly staff.  Haven't tried the food as we had a reservation but we decided to leave after we were seated on a table we objected to, and they refused to clean the table (with food remnants, snot and used tissues from previous guests).

reviews.title: Really nice restaurant in Amsterdam Noord. Nice staff, nice food but, be aware of two "small" details...
reviews.text:
Really nice restaurant in Amsterdam Noord. Nice staff, nice food but, be aware of two "small" details: 

1. if you are coming for dinner, be aware that the final price of the meal is different from the menu (my dinner was almost 10EUR more expensive because, according to the manager, some additional things "are not on the menu"). I never asked for fries and other things and even though, it came and I was charged for that.

2. QR-Code is mandatory in The Netherlands but it seems they don't ask this in the restaurant.

Maybe in future, I will come back.

reviews.title: Pleasant experience! Do recommend!
reviews.text:
Glow golf was very fun, although a bit short for 2 people. We finished around 45 min. I'm sure it would take longer with a bigger family. The 3D glasses are definitely worth it and make it a lot more challenging to play :)

The food was delicious, we had 2 burgers. Drinks are a little pricy, but that's okay. Definitely fun sitting in the cafe afterwards.
Staff was very friendly and helpful.
I do recommend coming here! Needs more positive reviews!

articleContent.title: A perfect day in Amsterdam

seoInfo.metaDescription: As a repeat visitor, I’ve never run out of reasons to return to Amsterdam. That’s because this city easily holds its own against other European capitals, thanks to its amazing architecture (especially those 17th-century canal houses), top-tier museums (all those Van Gogh sunflowers), and a dining scene that constantly punches above its weight. I’m always adding to my long list of places that I want to see when I visit my family here.

articleContent.title: 5 perfect days in Amsterdam

seoInfo.metaDescription: The Netherlands isn’t all tulips, windmills, and weed shops. With five days in Amsterdam you’ll go beyond the basics and see some of this capital city’s hidden delights. Yes, of course you’ll wander those iconic canals, stroll through street markets, and marvel at van Goghs, but you’ll also see street art in an abandoned shipyard and a tiny Catholic Church in the eaves of a 17th-century canal house.

articleContent.title: 7 perfect days in Amsterdam

seoInfo.metaDescription: Amsterdam is said to have two sides. There’s the charming side: quaint cobblestone streets that lead to picture-perfect canals lined with adorable gabled houses. And there’s the rowdy side: the lively Red Light District where you’ll find strip clubs and “coffee shops” selling cannabis. But there’s so much more to the city—like its many colorful outdoor markets, the street art in the once-abandoned shipyards of Amsterdam-Noord, and the bright tulip fields just beyond the capital. And with seven days, you’ll have the time to explore it all.
